How to create the repository quickly
	1.	Create a new repository on GitHub (e.g., langchain-local-hf-starter).
	2.	Clone it locally:

git clone git@github.com:YOUR_ORG/langchain-local-hf-starter.git
cd langchain-local-hf-starter


	3.	Create the file tree above and paste each file’s content.
	4.	Commit and push:

git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit: LangChain local HF RAG starter + devcontainer + CI"
git push origin main



After pushing, GitHub Actions will run the CI workflow on main (or you can run it manually via Actions → Your workflow → Run workflow).

